This paper deals with the problem of rendezvous, which is a fundamental problem in distributed computing. The paper focuses on the use of advice to achieve fast rendezvous, which is a topic that falls under the category of distributed algorithms. Therefore, cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of algorithms and information theory, which suggests that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.IT (Information Theory) are also likely sub-categories.
